"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-11-olympic-star-breaks-silence-fan-backlash-not-sharing-gold-medal-21403208\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"USathlete Shelby McEwen has defended his decision not to accept a shared gold medal atParis2024 which cost him the chance to beOlympicchampion.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 23, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelby_McEwen\", \"score\": 0.9999970370593713, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelby McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelby_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelby_McEwen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his decision\", \"from\": 37, \"to\": 49}, {\"ngram\": \"a shared gold medal\", \"from\": 64, \"to\": 83}, {\"ngram\": \"atParis2024\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 95}, {\"ngram\": \"the chance\", \"from\": 111, \"to\": 121}, {\"ngram\": \"beOlympicchampion\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 142}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McEwen was competing in the men's high jump final on Saturday night as the games drew to a close and was tied in first place withNew Zealand's Hamish Kerr after clearing the 2.36m jump.\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 145, \"end\": 151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"score\": 0.9999997229781841, \"rank\": 2.770218532235404e-07, \"text\": \"McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the men's high jump\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 188}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday night\", \"from\": 198, \"to\": 212}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 216, \"to\": 225}, {\"ngram\": \"a close\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 241}, {\"ngram\": \"first place\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 269}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2.36m jump\", \"from\": 315, \"to\": 329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both then failed to clear 2.38m and as they had the same number of failed jumps they were completely level.\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 439, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"2.38m\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"the same number\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 395}, {\"ngram\": \"failed jumps\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the 2024 Paris Olympics As a result, they had two choices: share the gold medal between them or compete in a jump-off, with both agreeing on the latter.\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 642, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 471}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 512}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 524}, {\"ngram\": \"two choices\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 546}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medal\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 568}, {\"ngram\": \"a jump-off\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It backfired on the American however, as he lost the jump-off and had to settle for the silver medal.\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 664, \"end\": 672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999997115808544, \"rank\": 2.6017318632498997e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the jump-off\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 705}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver medal\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His decision to snub a shared gold divided fans online, as while some could respect wanting to be an 'outright champion', others labelled the 28-year-old 'crazy'.\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His decision\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 759}, {\"ngram\": \"a shared gold divided fans\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"an 'outright champion\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 866}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But speaking at a press conference on Sunday, the final day of the games, McEwen insisted he had no regrets, saying: 'If it was meant to be it would have been.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 985, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"score\": 0.9999997229781841, \"rank\": 2.770218532235404e-07, \"text\": \"McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a press conference\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 955}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 983}, {\"ngram\": \"no regrets\", \"from\": 1008, \"to\": 1018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Shout out to Hamish for coming up to me, accepting a jump-off and I accepted it and I was all for it.\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hamish\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"a jump-off\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1134}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean, hey, he got the gold and I got the silver.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1225, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1203}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'At the end of the day, like he said it's a sport.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1277, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1276}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean I represent my country, just like he's representing his.\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my country\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1307}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am representing my family just like he's representing his.\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1402, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my family\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'At the end of the day we all want to be champions and the only respectful thing to do is walk away with one champion.'\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1523, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"champions\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"the only respectful thing\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1484}, {\"ngram\": \"one champion\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1521}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was in the men's high jump in Tokyo three years ago that Italy's Gianmarco Tamberi and Mutaz Essa Barshim of Qatar found themselves in the same situation as McEwen and Kerr, but on that occasion they opted to share the gold in amazing scenes.\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1558, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9788088089772473, \"rank\": 0.021643883594876977, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.888798208814429, \"rank\": 0.11011425616683723, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianmarco_Tamberi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gianmarco Tamberi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gianmarco_T